The paper deals with spatial-spectral fusion, which is a subfield of computer vision and image processing. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.MM) subcategories. Additionally, the use of an iterative optimization algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the focus on image fusion and the use of quantitative and visual assessments suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer graphics (cs.GR) subcategory, although this is less likely than the other categories mentioned.
